attr.attrdef: The PHYSICALID is designed to enable the creation of a centerline view and provide applications with a segment identifier that reflects the city's physical geography, including the individual roadbeds of divided streets. It is targeted particularly to support infrastructure applications at DOT, DEP and DDC.
Low Value for the hyphanated address range beginning on the left side of the street segment.
High Value for the hyphanated address range beginning on the left side of the street segment.
Low Value for the hyphanated address range beginning on the right side of the street segment.
High Value for the hyphanated address range beginning on the right side of the street segment.
Contains the five digit postal zip code for the left side of the street segment.
Contains the five digit postal zip code for the right side of the street segment.
Traffic Direction. Code indicating the flow of traffic relative to the street segment's address range.

edom.edomvd: With: Traffic flows from low to high house numbers.
Against: Traffic flows from high to low house numbers.
Two-Way: Traffic flows from high to low house numbers.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.
